@Node "Chart" "Chart & Statistics"


                                 @{B}C H A R T@{UB}

The new rating system has caused a lot of changes, but still Nerve Axis is
in the lead. Budbrain hit the 5th place thanks to their two crazy demos.

 Let's take a look at the previous datas:

                 @{B}Issue 1:@{UB}  61 demos - Average Rating: 2.54
                 @{B}Issue 2:@{UB} 122 demos - Average Rating: 2.48
                 @{B}Issue 3:@{UB} 153 demos - Average Rating: 2.52
                 @{B}Issue 4:@{UB} 213 demos - Average Rating: 2.69
                 @{B}Issue 5:@{UB} 249 demos - Average Rating: 2.61
                 @{B}Issue 6:@{UB} 290 demos - Average Rating: 2.71
                 @{B}Issue 7:@{UB} 335 demos - Average Rating: 2.73
                 @{B}Current:@{UB} 371 demos - Average Rating: 1.51 *

* Due to the new rating system it seems to have dropped a lot even though
  it hasn't!

@{B}---------------------------------------------------------------------------@{UB}

 Minimum two of a group's demos must have been reviewed in this guide to
 allow the group to enter the chart.
 This is an unfair chart: A group that has been around for a long time has
 made a lot of demos, both good and bad (everyone has to start somewhere),
 which means that they may score a low rank because their old demos (which
 are typically the worst, technically at least) tends to drag down the
 overall score.

@{B}---------------------------------------------------------------------------@{UB}

 >  =  Has gained one or more places since last issue
 <  =  Guess
 N  =  Newcomer
 (x)=  Last issues placing 

@{B}---------------------------------------------------------------------------@{UB}

