@Node "FAQ" "Frequently Asked Questions"

@{B}F@{UB}requently @{B}A@{UB}sked @{B}Q@{UB}uestions
--------------------------

@{B}Q: What is the purpose of this guide?@{UB}
@{B}A:@{UB} To guide you through the jungle of demos, to make it easier to choose
   the demos you like, to prevent you from downloading bad demos. It's kind
   of an encyclopedia.

@{B}Q: Who edits this guide?@{UB}
@{B}A:@{UB} We do. I (Dreyer) is the main-editor, DareDevil is co-editor, Shayera
   handles the Online version. NoName programmed the Guide Generator that is
   used to automatically sort and set up the reviews (NoName, there's a bug
   in it!).

@{B}Q: Why did you do it?@{UB}
@{B}A:@{UB} It's a hobby. I like watching demos, but dislike when the demo is
   obviously made as ugly as possible. To prevent others from watching
   those ugly, boring demos I created this guide. Also, it's a good way for
   me to exercise my English abilities.

@{B}Q: Is the size of the demos the crunched or uncrunched size?@{UB}
@{B}A:@{UB} Normally it's the uncrunched. It's the way I receive the demos I
   measure from.

@{B}Q: Are you influenced by any groups or persons who bribe you to get a
   better rating for their demo?@{UB}
@{B}A:@{UB} Yes, of course, we have to finance The Guide in some way :)
   Even though I'm a member of .sPOOn. I do not give any better rating than
   the demo deserves, that goes for all other groups aswell, and for all of
   the editors.

@{B}Q: How often is The Guide released? Where can I find it?@{UB}
@{B}A:@{UB} It's released 3-4 times a year, often at a major party. It's available
   at The Demo.Guide hompage (http://www.ssmedion.de/generation/) and at Aminet
   (Aminet:demo/mag/demoguide.lha).

@{B}Q: How do I become an editor?@{UB}
@{B}A:@{UB} Contact me (Dreyer) as soon as possible, or write to The Demo.Guide
   E-mail.

                                                                Dreyer

                         @{" Return to MAIN MENU " link "Main"}

@EndNode


@Help Help
@Node Help "Help - how to handle this guide"

                              @{B}The Main Menu@{UB}

 @{" Words from the Editor " link "words"} - An introduction to the current issue of this
                            guide.
 @{" Chart and Statistics " link "Chart"}  - A group and demo chart that shows which demos
                            has the highest ratings, and which groups that
                            have made the best production based on the
                            ratings.
 @{" Other Information " link "info"}    - Leads to a sub-directory where you can choose
                            from several different topics: Addresses,
                            credits, history, greetings, technical stuff,
                            requirements and installation, etc.
 @{" List sorted by... " link "main"}    - There are three buttons located to the right
                            called "List sorted by -Name -Group -Rating".
                            Click one of them and you'll get a list that is
                            sorted according to the chosen priority.

 @{" Search " system "lsags demoguide8rev2.guide"}               - Click this button to search the entire guide for
                            a word, name, etc. When pressed a requester pops
                            up. Write your search string in it and press
                            enter to start the search. It may take some
                            time. Be sure that the program LSAGS is in your
                            path (for example in C: or in the Demo.Guide
                            directory). LSAGS is not case sensitive.
 @{" Demo.Guide Online " link "Online"}    - A little page with information on the online-
                            version of this guide.


                          @{B}The Navigation buttons@{UB}

Those are the buttons located at the top of the window (and since you're
in the help menu you have already found it I guess).

Contents - Brings you to the Main Menu
Index    - Shows an alphabetically sorted list of links (no review links
           though).
Help     - Guess what! You'll enter this help text!
Retrace  - Click that once to get to the previous page
Browse   - There are two buttons called "Browse <" and "Browse >". Don't
           use any of these buttons. They'll lead you to the next page in
           in this guide, but since the structure is based on links rather
           than alphabetically sorted pages it is impossible to navigate
           using the Browse buttons.

                         @{" Return to MAIN MENU " link "Main"}

@EndNode


@Node "Reqs" "Requirements / Installation"

Installation:
-------------

@{B}The Demo.Guide@{UB}
Copy the Demo.Guide file to a directory (preferably its own directory)

@{B}The Demo.Guide pictures@{UB}
Copy the DemoGuidePics directory to the Demo.Guide's directory (so that it
 becomes a sub-directory).

Make sure that there's a path to @{B}Multiview@{UB} (or the viewer you use). If you
do not use Multiview change the Demo.Guide's default tool to the current
viewer by editing the icon information (click the icon once and choose
"information" from the Workbench menu). As the screenshots are set up to
using Multiview you are strongly adviced to have this viewer in the
Utilities-drawer of your boot partition (Sys:), if you do not have it there
you won't be able to see the screenshots.

@{B}The search engine@{UB}
Copy the file LSAGS to C: or The Demo.Guide directory.

Requirements:
-------------

@{B}The Demo.Guide@{UB}
- AmigaGuide-viewer or similar (preferably a new version)

@{B}The Demo.Guide pictures@{UB}
- GIF-datatype and JPG-datatype or -viewer
- The pictures @{B}must@{UB} be in a sub-directory of The Demo.Guide directory
  called @{B}DemoGuidePics@{UB}
  (e.g. Work:Scene/Demo.Guide/DemoGuidePics/)
  If they are not in that directory you won't be able to see the
  screenshots.

@EndNode


