@Node "History" "History of The Demo.Guide"

@{B}Issue # 1@{UB} - Created in a period of a couple of month, released May 01 on
            "Aminet:demo/mags/", where you can find all new issues of TDG.
            No. of demos:  61, overall demo rating: 2.54

@{B}Issue # 2@{UB} - Bugs removed, errors found and corrected.
            61 demos added! The overall quality of the reviewed demos
            dropped a bit (-0.06 points)!
            No. of demos: 122, overall demo rating: 2.48

@{B}Issue # 3@{UB} - Bugs removed (and added :)), screenshots added!
            31 demos added! The overall quality of the reviewed demos
            gained a little (+0.04 points)!
            No. of demos: 153, overall demo rating: 2.52

@{B}Issue # 4@{UB} - Bugs removed, non of them were fatal, though! New design to the
            Group Name-menu, redesign of other menus rejected. More
            screenshots added.
            60 demos added! The overall quality of the reviewed demos
            gained 0.17!
            No. of demos: 213, overall demo rating: 2.69

@{B}Issue # 5@{UB} - Released at The Party 7, including reviews from DareDevil and
            RockDaZone/Artwork.
            36 demos added! The overall quality of the reviewed demos
            dropped a bit (-0.08).
            No. of demos: 249, overall demo rating: 2.61

@{B}Issue # 6@{UB} - Released at Mekka/Symposium '98! Some unfortunate bugs were
            found. Hopefully that won't happen again!
            41 demos added! The overall quality of the reviewed demos
            gained 0.10!
            No. of demos: 290, overall demo rating: 2.71

@{B}Issue # 7@{UB} - The menus have been redesigned. The Help- and Index
            buttons have been made operational. Strange calculation errors
            removed, numbers corrected. TDG now has its own e-mail address.
            Shayera/.sPOOn. has taken over maintaining the Online-version
            (his first task was issue # 6, though)
            45 demos added! The overall quality of the reviewed demos
            gained a bit (+0.02)!
            No. of demos: 335, overall demo rating: 2.73

@{B}Issue # 8@{UB} - Released at Mekka/Symposium '98! A new rating system is now used. 
            36 demos added! The new rating system is incompatible with
            the old (can't be compared with each other). Rev. 2 contains
            bugfixes.
            No. of demos: 371, overall demo rating: 1.51

                       @{" Return to MAIN MENU " link "main"}

@Endnode


